ything about Trump or how much he claims to be worth. His refusal to releas=
e his returns breaks the precedent of every presidential candidate releasin=
g their returns dating back to 1972 =96 because, he claims, it=92s =93none =
of your business<https://www.google.com/url?sa=3Dt&rct=3Dj&q=3D&esrc=3Ds&so=
urce=3Dweb&cd=3D1&cad=3Drja&uact=3D8&ved=3D0ahUKEwi07oa0qubMAhVLGB4KHdoyBcM=
QFggcMAA&url=3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fpolitics%2Ffirst-draft%2F2016=
%2F05%2F13%2Fdonald-trump-on-his-tax-rate-its-none-of-your-business%2F&usg=
=3DAFQjCNH-AQd9DCxHeFp7rx7P9WuZBA_FDw&bvm=3Dbv.122448493,d.dmo>.=94

But it=92s not only that Donald Trump doesn=92t want to prove to us his wea=
lth or his tax rate; his PFDs yesterday show that Trump has been involved i=
n 100 lawsuits and he is profiting off of Chinese and Mexican companies =96=
 which begs the question, what else does Donald Trump have to hide?

The American people ought to know whether Trump has been paying his fair sh=
are and how much he would benefit from his own reckless tax plan. If Trump =
has nothing to hide, and if he claims to be as rich as he is, he will relea=
se his tax returns.

See what people are reading:


Details on Donald Trump=92s Finances Are Released, but Net Worth Is Unclear=
<http://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/19/us/politics/donald-trump-money.html>
